<paragraph id="8BB7368AD87EFFF13CB4FF6E3009FA60" blockId="43.[151,1058,211,263]" pageId="43" pageNumber="1002">D i a g n o s i s: The wide testaceous vitta on the elytral disc will distinguish the members of this species from congeners.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB7368AD87EFFF13CB4FEAD3176F909" blockId="43.[151,1059,278,623]" pageId="43" pageNumber="1002">
D e s c r i p t i o n: Size: Length 
<quantity id="4CF09B6FD87EFFF13E27FEAC306AFA4A" box="[516,597,278,300]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" pageId="43" pageNumber="1002" unit="mm" value="4.5">4.5 mm</quantity>
; width 
<quantity id="4CF09B6FD87EFFF13E82FEAC30CEFA4A" box="[673,753,278,300]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="43" pageNumber="1002" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
. Form: As in 
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD87EFFF13F5CFEAC31EBFA4D" box="[895,980,278,300]" captionStart="Figs 322-325" captionStartId="108.[151,191,1535,1557]" captionTargetBox="[153,1061,199,1522]" captionTargetId="figure@108.[153,1061,199,1522]" captionTargetPageId="108" captionText="Figs 322-325: Habitus; (322) Cregya livida; (323) C. maura; (324) C. petalosa; (325) C. tobagoensis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746822" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746822/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="1002">Fig. 324</figureCitation>
. Color: Cranium black. antenna bicolored, fundus and last antennomere yellow, antennomeres 8 and 9 brown; pronotum yellow, except pronotal arch black; mesosternum, femora, and abdomen yellow; metasternum, tibiae, and tarsi dark brown; elytra mostly dark brown, with broad testaceous vitta that extends from elytral posterior 2/3 
<superScript id="7C7D9BC2D87EFFF13F45FE3D314CFAF3" attach="left" box="[870,883,391,405]" fontSize="6" pageId="43" pageNumber="1002">rd</superScript>
to elytral basal margin; epipleural margin testaceous from humeral angle to posterior 2/3 
<superScript id="7C7D9BC2D87EFFF13FE7FE1F31EEFAD5" attach="none" box="[964,977,421,435]" fontSize="6" pageId="43" pageNumber="1002">rd</superScript>
. Head: Cranium finely punctate; antenna (
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD87EFFF13E31FE7C305CFABA" box="[530,611,454,476]" captionStart="Figs 43-60" captionStartId="72.[151,191,1361,1383]" captionTargetBox="[157,1053,222,1351]" captionTargetId="figure@72.[152,1057,206,1351]" captionTargetPageId="72" captionText="Figs 43-60: Antennae; (43) Ordinis taxis; (44) Pelonium tayrona; (45) Neorthopleura turnbowi, male; (46) N. turnbowi, female; (47) Megaphloeus imparilus; (48) Plocamocera catalexis; (48 a) Cregya entrerios; (49) Ridica merida. (50) Kataspinula puebla. (51) Cregya tobagoensis; (52) Topainca patchacutii; (53) Eurycaulis anaxeis; (54) Amboakis expandosa. (55) Ridica achira. (56) Ampleris cacuminis; (57) Sicamus suprus; (58) Sirpa latiflava; (59) Alarius careoritus; (60) Cregya petalosa." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746750" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746750/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="1002">Fig. 60</figureCitation>
) capitate, funicular antennomeres shorter towards capitulum, capitular antennomeres 8 and 9 large triangular, antennomere 10 ovoid; eyes large, coarsely facetted, eye narrower than frons (EW/FW 24/30). Thorax: Pronotum (
<figureCitation id="13332A0FD87EFFF13D2AFDA4335FF952" box="[265,352,542,564]" captionStart="Figs 101-117" captionStartId="75.[151,191,1477,1499]" captionTargetBox="[152,1030,198,1448]" captionTargetId="figure@75.[152,1030,198,1465]" captionTargetPageId="75" captionText="Figs 101-117: Pronota; (101) Aphelocerus ligulus; (102) A. yoro; (103) Ridica achira; (104) R. merida; (105) Ampleris cacuminis; (106) Plocamocera catalexis; (107) Aphelocerus tigra; (108) A. sparicapillus; (109) A. nolus; (110) A. magnipannus; (111) Pyticeroides desodes; (112) Cregya petalosa; (113) C. livida; (114) C. tobagoensis; (115) C. maura; (116) Pujoliclerus flavidus; (117) Amboakis collucoatis." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3746756" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3746756/files/figure.png" pageId="43" pageNumber="1002">Fig. 112</figureCitation>
) transverse (PW/PL 80/70), disc finely punctate, lateral tubercle well developed; elytra sculptured with 10 striae of asetiferous punctures that dissipate at elytral distal 3/4 
<superScript id="7C7D9BC2D87EFFF13D1FFDEF3376F905" attach="left" box="[316,329,597,611]" fontSize="6" pageId="43" pageNumber="1002">th</superScript>
(EL/EW 220/65). Abdomen: Pygidium scutiform.
</paragraph>
