<paragraph id="8BB7368AD87EFFF13CB4FD5D31FFF87F" blockId="43.[151,1058,742,793]" pageId="43" pageNumber="1002">
E t y m o l o g y: The trivial name, 
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D87EFFF13E0DFD5C30BBF99D" box="[558,644,742,763]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="1002">petalosa</emphasis>
, is a Greek adjective that stems from 
<emphasis id="B97CEA98D87EFFF13CB4FCB932DFF87E" box="[151,224,771,792]" italics="true" pageId="43" pageNumber="1002">petalos</emphasis>
(= broad); with reference to the wide testaceous vitta on the elytral disc.
</paragraph>
